trans-unit.source: Represents a 3-D rectangle: for example, a cube.
Rect3D is defined as a location (<xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Point3D>) and a size structure (<xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Size3D>).
trans-unit.target: Obiekcie Rect3D jest zdefiniowany jako lokalizacji (<xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Point3D>) i struktury rozmiarze (<xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Size3D>).</xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Size3D> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Point3D>

trans-unit.source: Because the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.X%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Y%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Z%2A> values specified for the size are magnitudes and not coordinates, they cannot be negative except in the case of an empty rectangle.
trans-unit.target: Ponieważ <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.X%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Y%2A>, i <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Z%2A>wartości określone dla rozmiaru wielkości i nie współrzędne, nie może być ujemna z wyjątkiem w przypadku pusty prostokąt.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Z%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Y%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.X%2A>

trans-unit.source: An empty rectangle is specified by <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Empty%2A>, which has <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.X%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Y%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Z%2A> values of -Infinity.
trans-unit.target: Określono pusty prostokąt za pomocą <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Empty%2A>, który ma <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.X%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Y%2A>, i <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Z%2A>wartości — wartości Infinity.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Z%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Y%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.X%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Rect3D.Empty%2A>

trans-unit.source: This structure is typically used to represent the bounds of a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.MeshGeometry3D> or <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Model3D>.
trans-unit.target: Ta struktura jest zwykle używana do reprezentowania granice <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.MeshGeometry3D>lub <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Model3D>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Model3D> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.MeshGeometry3D>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Size3D> and Rect3D are not typically used in XAML, because no settable properties exist in the WPF 3D object model that use those types.
